paragraphs.text: %md ## OML4SQL Data Transformation: convert variables from categorical to numerical In this notebook, we demonstrate how to convert a categorical variable to a numeric variable using Oracle SQL. We use the customer insurance lifetime value data set, which contains customer financial information, lifetime value, and whether or not the customer bought insurance. We show how to convert a categorical variable with each distinct level/value coded to an integer. Also, we show how to create an indicator variable based on a simple predicate. The dataset `CUSTOMER_INSURANCE_LTV_SQL` is generated by the `"OML Run-me-first"` notebook, which `MUST` be run before this notebook. --- ##### `IMPORTANT`: The `"OML Run-me-first"` notebook is available under the menu Templates -> Examples and is a pre-requisite to the current notebook. --- Copyright (c) 2023 Oracle Corporation ###### The Universal Permissive License (UPL), Version 1.0 ---

msg.data:
OML4SQL Data Transformation: convert variables from categorical to numerical

In this notebook, we demonstrate how to convert a categorical variable to a numeric variable using Oracle SQL.

We use the customer insurance lifetime value data set, which contains customer financial information, lifetime value, and whether or not the customer bought insurance.

We show how to convert a categorical variable with each distinct level/value coded to an integer. Also, we show how to create an indicator variable based on a simple predicate.

The dataset CUSTOMER_INSURANCE_LTV_SQL is generated by the "OML Run-me-first" notebook, which MUST be run before this notebook.

IMPORTANT: The "OML Run-me-first" notebook is available under the menu Templates -> Examples and is a pre-requisite to the current notebook.

paragraphs.title: Encode categorical column STATE using rownum
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT b.customer_id, a.state_code, a.state
FROM (
    SELECT rownum state_code,  state
    FROM (
        SELECT distinct state
        FROM CUSTOMER_INSURANCE_LTV_SQL ) d ) a
join CUSTOMER_INSURANCE_LTV_SQL b
ON a.state = b.state;

paragraphs.title: Create zero credit balance flag when the credit balance is zero
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT customer_id, 
       case when credit_balance = 0 then 1 else 0 end as zero_credit_balance, 
       credit_balance
FROM   CUSTOMER_INSURANCE_LTV_SQL
